cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.GR 

The paper discusses the use of deep learning methods, specifically convolutional neural networks (CNNs), for 3D point cloud classification. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. The paper also mentions the use of static terrestrial laser scanners for data acquisition, which falls under robotics (cs.RO). Additionally, the paper discusses the creation of a new benchmark data set, which could fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) or graphics (cs.GR) categories.
